IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: The mission of San Benito Health Foundation is to provide quality, affordable comprehensive health services to the community of San Benito County and surrounding areas in a manner that is accountable to the community while being respectful, empathetic, and culturally-sensitive to clients. Its vision is for safe and healthy San Benito County where health disparaties do not exist, people have access to care, and have the knowledge and skills to make healthy choices. The San Benito Health Foundation is a leader among alliances and partnerships that foster a climate of thoughtful change and create solutions for maintaining a community that is safe and healthy.

IRS990.Desc: Provided Medical,Ophthalmology, Preventive Medicine, Internal Medicine, Obstetrics & Gynecology, Family Planning, Pediatrics, Immunization & Health Screening Services, Nutrition Counseling, HIV/AIDS testing & counseling, Dental, Women, Infant and Children (WIC) Services to qualifying families of San Benito County and surrounding communities. Total patient encounters were as follows: Medical - 16,902, Dental - 647, Vision - 4,202, Patient Education - 43. SBHF has remained flexible and responsive to the community during the COVID-19 pandemic. Staff were redeployed to provide services via patient centered telehealth communications, it's immunization supply was increased to ensure protection of the community, and SBHF worked to teach patients how to communicate in case of a shelter in place order.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The accounting standard on accounting for uncertainty in income taxes addresses the determination of whether tax benefits claimed or expected to be claimed on a tax return should be recorded in the financial statements. Under the guidance, the Clinic may recognize the tax benefit from an uncertain tax position only if it is more likely than not that the tax position will be sustained on examination by taxing authorities based on the technical merits of the position. Examples of tax positions include the tax-exempt status of the Clinic and various positions related to the potential sources of unrelated business taxable income (UBIT). The tax benefits recognized in the financial statements from such a position are measured based on the largest benefit that has a greater than 50% likelihood of being realized upon ultimate settlement. There were no unrecognized tax benefits identified or recorded as liabilities for fiscal year 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 3
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Certain duties traditionally performed by the finance department were performed by FORVIS a consulting firm with expertise in the field. Duties performed included assisting with financial estimates, assisting the CEO with the budget process, preparation of monthly financial statements, and other financial reports as requested by funding agencies, and for providing technical support to the organization's accounting staff.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The form 990 is prepared by the independent accounting firm that conducts annual financial statement audit and information provided by the accounting department of the Health Center. Prior to filing, a tentative draft is reviewed by the president and CEO and the Executive Committee of the Board of Directors. Once any updates are made, a final draft will be provided to the full Board.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: All employees and Board of Directors of the Health Center are required to complete an annual conflict of interest statement of disclosure. This is kept in the personnel and board volunteer file. The Policy also includes the disclosure of conflicts of interest as they arise.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: An independent consulting agency, Merces Consulting, Inc. conducts annual salary survey and prepares the compensation scale as appropriate. Merces utilizes a systematic approach to employee compensation that involves the use of point factor job evaluation to assign jobs to pay grades, and surveys of the labor market to ensure that pay is competitive, methodologies for assessing individual pay levels on an annual basis. The Health Center retains Merces to review the competitive labor market and develop pay ranges for the upcoming year. Merces recommends the adoption of the new ranges to the Board of Directors who review the information provided, and consideration of adjustments to current compensation, where appropriate, to ensure that all employees are paid according to their contribution to the organization. The Board adopts changes to the compensation scale based on Merces's input. This procedure was last performed on July 2021. The Board aso reviews the performance of the Chief Executive Office and makes salary determinations based on the above mentioned methodology. The CEO's compensation was revewed using this procedure. The CEO evaluates key management employees on an annual basis and makes compensation determinations based on the above mentioned methodology as approved by the Board.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Health Center's governing documents and financial statements are made available upon request while keeping within the limits of HIPPA guidelines for protected information. All documents are available on an annual basis without restriction to the independent auditor.
